<html>
  <head>
    <title>Scribl-Er</title>
    <meta name="viewport" charset="utf-8" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#2e7d32">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/0.100.2/css/materialize.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/stylesheets/general-styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/public/stylesheets/codeStyles/code-styles.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <!-- Fixed Navbar with actions for manipulating data -->
      <div class="navbar-fixed">
        <nav class="green darken-3">
          <div class="nav-wrapper container">
            <a href="/" class="brand-logo left">Scribl-Er</a>
            <a href="#" data-activates="slide-out" class="button-collapse right"><i class="material-icons">menu</i></a>
            <ul class="right hide-on-med-and-down">
              <li class="waves-effect waves-light"><a class="modal-trigger" href="#console-modal">Console</a></li>
              <li class="waves-effect waves-light"><a class="modal-trigger space-right" href="#help-text">Help</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </nav>
      </div>
      <!-- When using navbar-fixed, side-nav must be outside of it in order to allow links to be clicked -->
      <ul id="slide-out" class="side-nav">
        <li><a class="modal-trigger" href="#console-modal">Console</a></li>
        <li><a class="modal-trigger space-right" href="#help-text">Help</a></li>
      </ul> <!-- end Nav -->
    </header>

    <main>
      <iframe id="html-viewer" sandbox="" srcdoc=""></iframe>
    </main>

    <!-- Code Console Modal -->
    <div id="console-modal" class="modal modal-fixed-footer bottom-sheet">
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m6">
            <div class="input-field">
              <textarea id="code-console" class="materialize-textarea" name="code"></textarea>
              <label for="code-console">Scribl-Er</label>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m6">
            <div class="input-field">
              <textarea id="console-output" class="materialize-textarea"></textarea>
              <label for="code-output">HTML</label>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <a href="#!" class="modal-action modal-close waves-effect waves-green btn-flat">Close</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Help Modal -->
    <div id="help-text" class="modal">
      <div class="modal-content">
        <h4>Instructions</h4>
        <h5>How to write Scribl-Er</h5>
        <p>Welcome to writing Scribl-Er. If you know how to write HTML, then you know Scribl-Er. All you need now is the syntax.</p>
        <p>The concept is the same as putting Python and HTML together. There are no brackets and white-space is important. Every tag is followed with a colon [ : ] and all displayed text is surrounded by double quotes [ " ]. Inline tags, such as spans, can be pushed inline using double parentheses [ ((span)) ]. To enclose tags inside of other tags, indent using the tab key. To force close a tag, you can use the semi-colon [ ; ].</p>
        <p><strong>Example</strong></p>
        <pre>
div id="main-content":
  h1: "Example Heading"
  hr:
  div id="example-code":
    p class="center-align":
      "This is some example text to show off Scribl-Er. You can use ((em: "inline")) characters to contain tags and text. You can also use syntax " strong: "like this"; " to also inline content."
  p: "Just remember that white-space is important. This content is not contained within the #example-code div."
        </pre>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <a href="#!" class="modal-action modal-close waves-effect btn-flat">Close</a>
      </div>
    </div>

